
New York, 2 Oct. 1780. Acknowledges a letter and congratulates TJ on Mrs: Jeffersons Health and recovery. Encloses further letters from Brig. Gen. Specht. Postscript (in French): Capt. Geismar had left New York before TJs letter containing kind remembrances of Geismar arrived; has had a letter from Geismar written from London, and has forwarded TJs message to him.
